The paper proposes a novel graph convolutional network (GCN) to tackle the label ambiguity challenge of General Partial Label Learning (GPLL). The problem formulation and proposed method involve machine learning, specifically deep learning and graph neural networks, which are commonly associated with the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.MM (Multimedia). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
